reviews.text: Yes, it is another building for shopping and dinning. Once you jump on here, you can spend all your day long here shopping luxury goods, watching movies, and enjoying and dinning from luxury high end cuisine to budget restaurant and even sweety desert. And there are supermarket and small souvenirs shops too. There are some shops where you may experience only this place.
most convenient shopping mall with great restaurants

Very nice song mall with a wide array of styles of shops and levels of cost. It also has a cinema inside, several floors for restaurants and tea/dessert options, as well as four luxury restaurants with harbour views at the very top floors. Always a pleasant place and an option when around TST.
One stop for shopping and restaurants for every taste and any budget

Facing both nathan road and granville road corner. Nearest MTR station is Tsim Sha Tsui station Exit B2.

result.name: Broadway Cinema

reviews.text: As a disabled with power wheelchair, I wish to take this opportunity to express my sincere gratitude to Charis and Collen for their assistance. With their care and assistance, l can enjoy the excellent movie i.e. Still Human in Broadway, The One in the morning of 11May 2019.

Rather small sized cinema. The chair was comfortable and the air was ok, but the screen size was small, that was fixed to small sized theater.

Good choices of popcorn and beverage are here. And it offers even simple dimsum and hotdogs. Staffs were nice.

It is located around a shopping mall, so that you may hang around after buying the tickets.

Arrived at 8pm for the 8.15 movie at the 10th floor, tried taking the elevator; first one took me to the fourth. Second one took 12 minutes to take me to the 10th. Arrived 8.31 at the theater. Too late. Shucks.
Comfotable seating, like a lecture hall so people sitting in front won't block your view!
Nice place to go especially for senior citizens.
